17:T400,In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:

netfilter: nf_tables: fix inverted genmask check in nft_map_catchall_activate()

nft_map_catchall_activate() has an inverted element activity check
compared to its non-catchall counterpart nft_mapelem_activate() and
compared to what is logically required.

nft_map_catchall_activate() is called from the abort path to re-activate
catchall map elements that were deactivated during a failed transaction.
It should skip elements that are already active (they don't need
re-activation) and process elements that are inactive (they need to be
restored). Instead, the current code does the opposite: it skips inactive
elements and processes active ones.

Compare the non-catchall activate callback, which is correct:

  nft_mapelem_activate():
    if (nft_set_elem_active(ext, iter->genmask))
        return 0;   /* skip active, process inactive */

With the buggy catchall version:

  nft_map_catchall_activate():
    if (!nft_set_elem_active(ext, genmask))
 18:T400,Strapi is an open source headless content management system. Strapi versions starting in 4.0.0 and prior to 5.37.0 did not sufficiently sanitize query parameters when filtering content via relational fields. An unauthenticated attacker could use the `where` query parameter on any publicly-accessible content-type with an `updatedBy` (or other admin-relation) field to perform a boolean-oracle attack against private fields on the joined `admin_users` table, including the `resetPasswordToken` field. Extracting an admin reset token via this oracle made full administrative account takeover possible without authentication. When a filter such as `where[updatedBy][resetPasswordToken][$startsWith]=a` was applied to a public Content API endpoint, the underlying query generation performed a `LEFT JOIN` against the `admin_users` table and emitted a `WHERE` clause referencing the joined column. The query parameter sanitization layer did not block operator chains that traversed into relational target schemas the caller had 19:T406,The Hippoo Mobile App for WooCommerce plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to Authentication Bypass leading to Administrator Account Takeover in all versions up to and including 1.9.4. This is due to a logic conflation in HippooPermissions::get_user_permissions(), which returns the same null sentinel for both administrators and unauthenticated visitors — a value that HippooPermissions::has_role_access() unconditionally interprets as full administrator access — causing override_extension_permission_callback() to assign __return_true as the permission callback for every WordPress and WooCommerce REST route cloned under /wc-hippoo/v1/ext/ by HippooControllerWithAuth::re_register_external_routes(), while the block_unauthorized_access() pre-dispatch guard fails to block unauthenticated users for the same reason. This makes it possible for unauthenticated attackers to invoke any core REST endpoint without credentials — most critically, sending a POST request to /wc-hippoo/v1/ext/wp/v2/users/<id> with a {"password":"<1a:T400,Improper Input Validation, Improper Control of Generation of Code ('Code Injection') vulnerability in Apache ActiveMQ Broker, Apache ActiveMQ.

Apache ActiveMQ Classic exposes the Jolokia JMX-HTTP bridge at /api/jolokia/ on the web console. The default Jolokia access policy permits exec operations on all ActiveMQ MBeans (org.apache.activemq:*), including
BrokerService.addNetworkConnector(String) and BrokerService.addConnector(String).

An authenticated attacker can invoke these operations with a crafted discovery URI that triggers the VM transport's brokerConfig parameter to load a remote Spring XML application context using ResourceXmlApplicationContext.
Because Spring's ResourceXmlApplicationContext instantiates all singleton beans before the BrokerService validates the configuration, arbitrary code execution occurs on the broker's JVM through bean factory methods such as Runtime.exec().



This issue affects Apache ActiveMQ Broker: before 5.19.4, from 6.0.0 before 6.2.3; Apache ActiveMQ All: before 5.19.4,1b:T401,Improper Input Validation, Improper Control of Generation of Code ('Code Injection') vulnerability in Apache ActiveMQ Broker, Apache ActiveMQ All, Apache ActiveMQ.

Apache ActiveMQ Classic exposes the Jolokia JMX-HTTP bridge at /api/jolokia/ on the web console. The default Jolokia access policy permits exec operations on all ActiveMQ MBeans (org.apache.activemq:*), including
BrokerService.addNetworkConnector(String).

An authenticated attacker can invoke these operations with a crafted discovery URI that triggers the VM transport's brokerConfig parameter using the "masterslave:// " URL which can allow loading a Spring XML application context using ResourceXmlApplicationContext.
Because Spring's ResourceXmlApplicationContext instantiates all singleton beans before the BrokerService validates the configuration, arbitrary code execution occurs on the broker's JVM through bean factory methods such as Runtime.exec().
This issue affects Apache ActiveMQ Broker: before 5.19.7, from 6.0.0 before 6.2.6; Apache ActiveMQ1c:T400,A vulnerability in the CLI of Cisco Catalyst SD-WAN Manager, formerly SD-WAN vManage, could allow an authenticated, local attacker to execute arbitrary commands as root by supplying a crafted file to the affected system.

This vulnerability is due to insufficient validation of user-supplied input. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability by uploading a crafted file to the affected system. A successful exploit could allow the attacker to perform command injection attacks on an affected system and elevate their privileges as the root user.
To exploit this vulnerability, the attacker must have netadmin privileges on the affected system. This would require valid credentials or exploitation of  or . Cisco is not aware of successful exploitation by other methods. Cisco has observed limited cases where the exploitation of this bug resulted in a configuration change pushed to edge devices.
Cisco recommends that customers upgrade to the fixed software that is documented in the  that was published on May 14, 201d:T400,web3.py allows you to interact with the Ethereum blockchain using Python. From 6.0.0b3 to before 7.15.0 and 8.0.0b2, web3.py implements CCIP Read / OffchainLookup (EIP-3668) by performing HTTP requests to URLs supplied by smart contracts in offchain_lookup_payload["urls"]. The implementation uses these contract-supplied URLs directly (after {sender} / {data} template substitution) without any destination validation. CCIP Read is enabled by default (global_ccip_read_enabled = True on all providers), meaning any application using web3.py's .call() method is exposed without explicit opt-in. This results in Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) when web3.py is used in backend services, indexers, APIs, or any environment that performs eth_call / .call() against untrusted or user-supplied contract addresses. A malicious contract can force the web3.py process to issue HTTP requests to arbitrary destinations, including internal network services and cloud metadata endpoints. This vulnerability is fixed in 7.15.0 and 8.0.c:["$","main",null,{"children":["$","$L16",null,{"initialData":[{"id":"1263630897","cve_id":"CVE-2026-47429","name":"cve-lite-on-pi","owner":"az9713","full_name":"az9713/cve-lite-on-pi","html_url":"https://github.com/az9713/cve-lite-on-pi","description":"Running OWASP cve-lite-cli against the pi monorepo: scan journey and key finding (vitest CVE-2026-47429).","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-06-09 15:04:36","updated_at":"2026-06-09 15:09:44","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 15:09:41","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 16:36:41","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1263596705","cve_id":"CVE-2022-39996","name":"Teldat-Router-CVE-2022-POC","owner":"uyhacked","full_name":"uyhacked/Teldat-Router-CVE-2022-POC","html_url":"https://github.com/uyhacked/Teldat-Router-CVE-2022-POC","description":"POC for CVE-2022-39996 (Reflected XSS) and CVE-2022-39997 (Weak Password) in Teldat RS123/RS123w Router","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Cross Site Scripting vulnerability in Teldats Router RS123, RS123w allows attacker to execute arbitrary code via the cmdcookie parameter to the upgrade/query.php page.","created_at":"2026-06-09 14:13:44","updated_at":"2026-06-09 14:43:37","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 14:43:33","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 16:36:39","cvss_score":4.8,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1263582601","cve_id":"CVE-2025-43529","name":"CVE-2025-43529-no-forked","owner":"junfuture1103","full_name":"junfuture1103/CVE-2025-43529-no-forked","html_url":"https://github.com/junfuture1103/CVE-2025-43529-no-forked","description":"CVE-2025-43529 safari fakeobj","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A use-after-free issue was addressed with improved memory management. This issue is fixed in watchOS 26.2, Safari 26.2, iOS 18.7.3 and iPadOS 18.7.3, iOS 26.2 and iPadOS 26.2, macOS Tahoe 26.2, visionOS 26.2, tvOS 26.2. Processing maliciously crafted web content may lead to arbitrary code execution. Apple is aware of a report that this issue may have been exploited in an extremely sophisticated attack against specific targeted individuals on versions of iOS before iOS 26. CVE-2025-14174 was also issued in response to this report.","created_at":"2026-06-09 13:50:56","updated_at":"2026-06-09 13:51:16","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 13:50:57","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 16:36:41","cvss_score":8.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1263536798","cve_id":"CVE-2026-45067","name":"CVE-2026-45067","owner":"HORKimhab","full_name":"HORKimhab/CVE-2026-45067","html_url":"https://github.com/HORKimhab/CVE-2026-45067","description":"CVE-2026-45067 - Draft","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-06-09 12:35:26","updated_at":"2026-06-09 12:35:32","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 12:35:29","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 16:36:41","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1263535547","cve_id":"CVE-2024-52011","name":"CVE-2024-52011","owner":"HORKimhab","full_name":"HORKimhab/CVE-2024-52011","html_url":"https://github.com/HORKimhab/CVE-2024-52011","description":"CVE-2024-52011 - Draft","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"launch-editor allows users to open files with line numbers in editor from Node.js. Prior to version 2.9.0, due to the insufficient sanitization of the `file` argument in the `launchEditor`, an attacker can execute arbitrary commands on Windows by supplying a filename that contains special characters. This issue has been fixed in the `launch-editor` version 2.9.0, corresponding to vite version 5.4.9.","created_at":"2026-06-09 12:33:21","updated_at":"2026-06-09 12:33:29","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 12:33:25","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 16:36:40","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1263531835","cve_id":"CVE-2026-8054","name":"CVE-2026-8054","owner":"Mr-xn","full_name":"Mr-xn/CVE-2026-8054","html_url":"https://github.com/Mr-xn/CVE-2026-8054","description":"dotCMS Pre-auth SQL Injection","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection') in the Publish Audit API endpoints (/api/auditPublishing/get and /api/auditPublishing/getAll) in dotCMS Core 25.11.04-1 through 26.04.28-02 allows remote unauthenticated attackers to read, modify, or destroy arbitrary database content. The endpoints did not enforce authentication and accepted unsanitized input used in dynamically constructed SQL. The fix in dotCMS Core 26.04.28-03 requires an authenticated backend user with the publishing-queue portlet permission. LTS releases are not affected as the vulnerable code path was never backported.","created_at":"2026-06-09 12:27:09","updated_at":"2026-06-09 12:28:42","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 12:27:49","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 16:36:41","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1263460848","cve_id":"CVE-2026-23111","name":"CVE-2026-23111","owner":"HORKimhab","full_name":"HORKimhab/CVE-2026-23111","html_url":"https://github.com/HORKimhab/CVE-2026-23111","description":"CVE-2026-23111 - Linux - Draft","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$17","created_at":"2026-06-09 10:25:18","updated_at":"2026-06-09 10:25:25","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 10:25:22","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 16:36:41","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1263432393","cve_id":"CVE-2025-59528","name":"CVE-2025-59528","owner":"Moon-Harvest","full_name":"Moon-Harvest/CVE-2025-59528","html_url":"https://github.com/Moon-Harvest/CVE-2025-59528","description":"Go Proof of Concept (PoC) exploit for Flowise CustomMCP Remote Code Execution (RCE) CVE-2025-59528","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Flowise is a drag & drop user interface to build a customized large language model flow. In version 3.0.5, Flowise is vulnerable to remote code execution. The CustomMCP node allows users to input configuration settings for connecting to an external MCP server. This node parses the user-provided mcpServerConfig string to build the MCP server configuration. However, during this process, it executes JavaScript code without any security validation. Specifically, inside the convertToValidJSONString function, user input is directly passed to the Function() constructor, which evaluates and executes the input as JavaScript code. Since this runs with full Node.js runtime privileges, it can access dangerous modules such as child_process and fs. This issue has been patched in version 3.0.6.","created_at":"2026-06-09 09:31:54","updated_at":"2026-06-09 09:42:31","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 09:42:27","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 10:36:42","cvss_score":10,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1263172501","cve_id":"CVE-2026-24061","name":"CVE-2026-24061-GNU-InetUtils-telnetd","owner":"achnouri","full_name":"achnouri/CVE-2026-24061-GNU-InetUtils-telnetd","html_url":"https://github.com/achnouri/CVE-2026-24061-GNU-InetUtils-telnetd","description":"GNU-InetUtils-telnetd-Authentication-Bypass-Vulnerability","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"telnetd in GNU Inetutils through 2.7 allows remote authentication bypass via a \"-f root\" value for the USER environment variable.","created_at":"2026-06-09 02:36:36","updated_at":"2026-06-09 03:50:47","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 03:46:26","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 04:36:42","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1263141438","cve_id":"CVE-2024-0258","name":"CVE-2024-0258-Research","owner":"aliyabuz25","full_name":"aliyabuz25/CVE-2024-0258-Research","html_url":"https://github.com/aliyabuz25/CVE-2024-0258-Research","description":"Research and analysis of CVE-2024-0258, a libxpc memory handling vulnerability that could allow sandbox escape and elevated privilege execution.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The issue was addressed with improved memory handling. This issue is fixed in iOS 17.4 and iPadOS 17.4, macOS Sonoma 14.4, tvOS 17.4, watchOS 10.4. An app may be able to execute arbitrary code out of its sandbox or with certain elevated privileges.","created_at":"2026-06-09 01:59:22","updated_at":"2026-06-09 02:04:10","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 02:00:02","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 04:36:40","cvss_score":8.2,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1263138857","cve_id":"CVE-2026-4480","name":"CVE-2026-4480","owner":"CarlosEduardoPM","full_name":"CarlosEduardoPM/CVE-2026-4480","html_url":"https://github.com/CarlosEduardoPM/CVE-2026-4480","description":"smb spooler to RCE","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A flaw was found in the Samba printing subsystem. Samba passes the client-controlled job description string to the command configured with the \"print command\" setting via the \"%J\"\nsubstitution character without escaping shell meta characters. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability by sending a specially crafted print job description that contains unescaped shell characters. This could lead to remote code execution on the affected system.","created_at":"2026-06-09 01:56:28","updated_at":"2026-06-09 03:08:05","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 03:08:01","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 04:36:42","cvss_score":9,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1263040329","cve_id":"CVE-2026-24061","name":"CVE-2026-24061","owner":"K3ysTr0K3R","full_name":"K3ysTr0K3R/CVE-2026-24061","html_url":"https://github.com/K3ysTr0K3R/CVE-2026-24061","description":"A PoC exploit for CVE-2026-24061 - GNU InetUtils telnetd Argument Injection Authentication Bypass","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"telnetd in GNU Inetutils through 2.7 allows remote authentication bypass via a \"-f root\" value for the USER environment variable.","created_at":"2026-06-09 00:04:56","updated_at":"2026-06-09 00:30:56","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 00:28:15","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 04:36:42","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1263020786","cve_id":"CVE-2026-49975","name":"CVE-2026-49975-HTTP-2-Bomb","owner":"renzi25031469","full_name":"renzi25031469/CVE-2026-49975-HTTP-2-Bomb","html_url":"https://github.com/renzi25031469/CVE-2026-49975-HTTP-2-Bomb","description":"Disclosed on June 3, 2026, the \"HTTP/2 Bomb\" is an unauthenticated remote DoS that combines an HPACK compression bomb with a Slowloris-style hold to exhaust server memory. It affects default HTTP/2 configurations of **nginx, Apache httpd, Microsoft IIS, Envoy, and Cloudflare Pingora**.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Memory Allocation with Excessive Size Value vulnerability in Apache HTTP Server's mod_http leads to denial of service via malicious HTTP requests.\n\nThis issue affects Apache HTTP Server: from 2.4.17 through 2.4.67.","created_at":"2026-06-08 23:44:32","updated_at":"2026-06-09 00:01:48","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 23:58:44","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 04:36:42","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1263011916","cve_id":"CVE-2026-50751","name":"CVE-2026-50751","owner":"0xBlackash","full_name":"0xBlackash/CVE-2026-50751","html_url":"https://github.com/0xBlackash/CVE-2026-50751","description":"CVE-2026-50751","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A logic flow weakness in Remote Access and Mobile Access certificate validation in deprecated IKEv1 key exchange allows an unauthenticated remote attacker to bypass user authentication and establish a remote access VPN connection without a valid user password.","created_at":"2026-06-08 23:35:04","updated_at":"2026-06-09 00:22:22","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 00:21:41","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 04:36:42","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262948432","cve_id":"CVE-2026-50751","name":"CVE-2026-50751-Mitigation-Scripts","owner":"WadesWeaponShed","full_name":"WadesWeaponShed/CVE-2026-50751-Mitigation-Scripts","html_url":"https://github.com/WadesWeaponShed/CVE-2026-50751-Mitigation-Scripts","description":"Mitigation scripts for CVE-2026-50751","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":"A logic flow weakness in Remote Access and Mobile Access certificate validation in deprecated IKEv1 key exchange allows an unauthenticated remote attacker to bypass user authentication and establish a remote access VPN connection without a valid user password.","created_at":"2026-06-08 22:26:38","updated_at":"2026-06-09 03:22:11","pushed_at":"2026-06-09 01:06:59","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 04:36:42","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262919926","cve_id":"CVE-2026-27886","name":"CVE-2026-27886-PoC-Account-Takeover","owner":"thesw0rd","full_name":"thesw0rd/CVE-2026-27886-PoC-Account-Takeover","html_url":"https://github.com/thesw0rd/CVE-2026-27886-PoC-Account-Takeover","description":"Account takeover full PoC for CVE-2026-27886 in Strapi CMS","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$18","created_at":"2026-06-08 21:55:27","updated_at":"2026-06-08 22:02:54","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 22:02:50","inserted_at":"2026-06-09 04:36:42","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262908394","cve_id":"CVE-2026-45585","name":"YellowKey-BitLocker-Bypass-CVE-2026-45585-Detect-Fix-Automatically-via-Microsoft-Intune","owner":"ChanderManiPandey2022","full_name":"ChanderManiPandey2022/YellowKey-BitLocker-Bypass-CVE-2026-45585-Detect-Fix-Automatically-via-Microsoft-Intune","html_url":"https://github.com/ChanderManiPandey2022/YellowKey-BitLocker-Bypass-CVE-2026-45585-Detect-Fix-Automatically-via-Microsoft-Intune","description":"YellowKey | BitLocker Bypass CVE-2026-45585 | Detect & Fix Automatically via Microsoft Intune","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Microsoft is aware of a security feature bypass vulnerability in Windows publicly referred to as &quot;YellowKey&quot;. The proof of concept for this vulnerability has been made public violating coordinated vulnerability best practices.\nWe are issuing this CVE to provide mitigation guidance that can be implemented to protect against this vulnerability until the security update is made available.","created_at":"2026-06-08 21:42:23","updated_at":"2026-06-08 21:42:49","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 21:43:38","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:42","cvss_score":6.8,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1262851960","cve_id":"CVE-2023-21716","name":"CVE-2023-21716","owner":"REGGYRAIDER","full_name":"REGGYRAIDER/CVE-2023-21716","html_url":"https://github.com/REGGYRAIDER/CVE-2023-21716","description":"CVE-2023-21716 - Microsoft Word RTF fonttbl Heap Corruption RCE exploit with reverse shell payload","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Microsoft Word Remote Code Execution Vulnerability","created_at":"2026-06-08 20:37:09","updated_at":"2026-06-08 20:37:54","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 20:37:52","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:40","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1262817546","cve_id":"CVE-2026-11499","name":"CVE-2026-11499","owner":"0xBlackash","full_name":"0xBlackash/CVE-2026-11499","html_url":"https://github.com/0xBlackash/CVE-2026-11499","description":"CVE-2026-11499","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A vulnerability was determined in Tenda HG7HG9 and HG10 300001138_en_xpon. This affects the function formDOMAINBLK of the file /boaform/formDOMAINBLK. Executing a manipulation of the argument blkDomain can lead to stack-based buffer overflow. The attack may be performed from remote.","created_at":"2026-06-08 19:54:48","updated_at":"2026-06-08 20:03:37","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 20:03:33","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:42","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1262795457","cve_id":"CVE-2025-43537","name":"CVE-2025-43537","owner":"hawkeye-bd","full_name":"hawkeye-bd/CVE-2025-43537","html_url":"https://github.com/hawkeye-bd/CVE-2025-43537","description":"Cybersecurity Researcher | Apple Security Credit (CVE-2025-43537) | Vulnerability Research & Responsible Disclosure","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A path handling issue was addressed with improved validation. This issue is fixed in iOS 18.7.5 and iPadOS 18.7.5, iOS 26.2 and iPadOS 26.2. Restoring a maliciously crafted backup file may lead to modification of protected system files.","created_at":"2026-06-08 19:26:38","updated_at":"2026-06-08 19:32:08","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 19:32:04","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:41","cvss_score":3.5,"severity":"LOW"},{"id":"1262791979","cve_id":"CVE-2025-57819","name":"FreePBX-CVE-2025-57819","owner":"YuvrajSHAD","full_name":"YuvrajSHAD/FreePBX-CVE-2025-57819","html_url":"https://github.com/YuvrajSHAD/FreePBX-CVE-2025-57819","description":"Unauthenticated SQL Injection to Remote Code Execution in FreePBX — CVE-2025-57819","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"FreePBX is an open-source web-based graphical user interface. FreePBX 15, 16, and 17 endpoints are vulnerable due to insufficiently sanitized user-supplied data allowing unauthenticated access to FreePBX Administrator leading to arbitrary database manipulation and remote code execution. This issue has been patched in endpoint versions 15.0.66, 16.0.89, and 17.0.3.","created_at":"2026-06-08 19:22:14","updated_at":"2026-06-08 19:30:35","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 19:30:32","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:42","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262756923","cve_id":"CVE-2024-33421","name":"CVE-2024-33421","owner":"sp624","full_name":"sp624/CVE-2024-33421","html_url":"https://github.com/sp624/CVE-2024-33421","description":"Stored XSS in Computer Laboratory Management System - v1.0","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-06-08 18:40:46","updated_at":"2026-06-08 18:56:11","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 18:56:07","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:41","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262738235","cve_id":"CVE-2024-31509","name":"CVE-2024-31509","owner":"sp624","full_name":"sp624/CVE-2024-31509","html_url":"https://github.com/sp624/CVE-2024-31509","description":"SQL Injection in computer-laboratory-management-system-using-php-and-mysql - LMS - PHP  v1.0","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-06-08 18:19:05","updated_at":"2026-06-08 18:29:49","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 18:29:13","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:41","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262732203","cve_id":"CVE-2025-32433","name":"CVE-2025-32433-Exploit-edited","owner":"chuzouX","full_name":"chuzouX/CVE-2025-32433-Exploit-edited","html_url":"https://github.com/chuzouX/CVE-2025-32433-Exploit-edited","description":"Based on the original version:https://github.com/vulhub/vulhub/blob/master/erlang/CVE-2025-32433/exploit.py Replace Unicode checkmark with ASCII character for Windows compatibility","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Erlang/OTP is a set of libraries for the Erlang programming language. Prior to versions OTP-27.3.3, OTP-26.2.5.11, and OTP-25.3.2.20, a SSH server may allow an attacker to perform unauthenticated remote code execution (RCE). By exploiting a flaw in SSH protocol message handling, a malicious actor could gain unauthorized access to affected systems and execute arbitrary commands without valid credentials. This issue is patched in versions OTP-27.3.3, OTP-26.2.5.11, and OTP-25.3.2.20. A temporary workaround involves disabling the SSH server or to prevent access via firewall rules.","created_at":"2026-06-08 18:11:36","updated_at":"2026-06-08 18:21:38","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 18:21:32","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:41","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262730128","cve_id":"CVE-2008-1930","name":"CVE-2008-1930","owner":"HeisenbergH4X","full_name":"HeisenbergH4X/CVE-2008-1930","html_url":"https://github.com/HeisenbergH4X/CVE-2008-1930","description":"CVE-2008-1930 is a critical improper authentication vulnerability affecting the core cookie integrity mechanism in WordPress version 2.5. It allows remote attackers to bypass security controls, forge authentication cookies, and gain unauthorized administrator privileges on an affected website.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-06-08 18:09:05","updated_at":"2026-06-08 18:09:39","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 18:09:36","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:37","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262563402","cve_id":"CVE-2018-16763","name":"CVE-2018-16763","owner":"SOME-1HING","full_name":"SOME-1HING/CVE-2018-16763","html_url":"https://github.com/SOME-1HING/CVE-2018-16763","description":"Python tool for analyzing CVE-2018-16763 in FUEL CMS with cleaner response parsing and interactive vulnerability checking.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"FUEL CMS 1.4.1 allows PHP Code Evaluation via the pages/select/ filter parameter or the preview/ data parameter. This can lead to Pre-Auth Remote Code Execution.","created_at":"2026-06-08 14:29:13","updated_at":"2026-06-08 14:34:19","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 14:34:16","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:38","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262562060","cve_id":"CVE-2025-5878","name":"ESAPI-SQLinjection-CVE-2025-5878-Exploit","owner":"dickfu","full_name":"dickfu/ESAPI-SQLinjection-CVE-2025-5878-Exploit","html_url":"https://github.com/dickfu/ESAPI-SQLinjection-CVE-2025-5878-Exploit","description":"针对ESAPI 的ESAPI.encoder().encodeForSQL()方法，OracleCodec对象的sql 时间盲注利用","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A vulnerability was found in ESAPI esapi-java-legacy and classified as problematic. This issue affects the interface Encoder.encodeForSQL of the SQL Injection Defense. An attack leads to an improper neutralization of special elements. The attack may be initiated remotely and an exploit has been disclosed to the public. The project was contacted early about this issue and handled it with an exceptional level of professionalism. Upgrading to version 2.7.0.0 is able to address this issue. Commit ID f75ac2c2647a81d2cfbdc9c899f8719c240ed512 is disabling the feature by default and any attempt to use it will trigger a warning. And commit ID e2322914304d9b1c52523ff24be495b7832f6a56 is updating the misleading Java class documentation to warn about the risks.","created_at":"2026-06-08 14:26:59","updated_at":"2026-06-08 17:38:47","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 17:38:44","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 22:36:42","cvss_score":7.3,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1262374495","cve_id":"CVE-2026-4480","name":"CVE-2026-4480","owner":"0xBlackash","full_name":"0xBlackash/CVE-2026-4480","html_url":"https://github.com/0xBlackash/CVE-2026-4480","description":"CVE-2026-4480","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A flaw was found in the Samba printing subsystem. Samba passes the client-controlled job description string to the command configured with the \"print command\" setting via the \"%J\"\nsubstitution character without escaping shell meta characters. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability by sending a specially crafted print job description that contains unescaped shell characters. This could lead to remote code execution on the affected system.","created_at":"2026-06-08 08:20:01","updated_at":"2026-06-08 08:27:32","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 08:27:29","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 10:36:42","cvss_score":9,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1262246854","cve_id":"CVE-2011-2523","name":"pwntilldawn-10.150.150.12","owner":"kmrlbhr","full_name":"kmrlbhr/pwntilldawn-10.150.150.12","html_url":"https://github.com/kmrlbhr/pwntilldawn-10.150.150.12","description":"PwnTillDawn walkthrough — 10.150.150.12 (portal) | vsftpd 2.3.4 backdoor CVE-2011-2523","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"vsftpd 2.3.4 downloaded between 20110630 and 20110703 contains a backdoor which opens a shell on port 6200/tcp.","created_at":"2026-06-08 03:55:43","updated_at":"2026-06-08 03:58:50","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 03:58:47","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 10:36:37","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262208973","cve_id":"CVE-2025-57819","name":"freepbx-endpoint-sqli-rce","owner":"jf-gondim","full_name":"jf-gondim/freepbx-endpoint-sqli-rce","html_url":"https://github.com/jf-gondim/freepbx-endpoint-sqli-rce","description":"Unauthenticated SQL injection in FreePBX Endpoint Manager (CVE-2025-57819) that injects a cron-scheduled PHP webshell for remote code execution.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"FreePBX is an open-source web-based graphical user interface. FreePBX 15, 16, and 17 endpoints are vulnerable due to insufficiently sanitized user-supplied data allowing unauthenticated access to FreePBX Administrator leading to arbitrary database manipulation and remote code execution. This issue has been patched in endpoint versions 15.0.66, 16.0.89, and 17.0.3.","created_at":"2026-06-08 02:56:19","updated_at":"2026-06-08 02:58:29","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 02:58:25","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 04:36:40","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1262132734","cve_id":"CVE-2020-17103","name":"CVE-2020-17103","owner":"0xBlackash","full_name":"0xBlackash/CVE-2020-17103","html_url":"https://github.com/0xBlackash/CVE-2020-17103","description":"CVE-2020-17103","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Windows Cloud Files Mini Filter Driver Elevation of Privilege Vulnerability","created_at":"2026-06-08 01:05:30","updated_at":"2026-06-08 01:32:47","pushed_at":"2026-06-08 01:32:44","inserted_at":"2026-06-08 04:36:38","cvss_score":7,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1261982856","cve_id":"CVE-2026-9082","name":"CVE-2026-9082","owner":"11romain","full_name":"11romain/CVE-2026-9082","html_url":"https://github.com/11romain/CVE-2026-9082","description":"Drupal Core PostgreSQL SQLi to RCE via /user/login (CVE-2026-9082 / SA-CORE-2026-004)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection') vulnerability in Drupal Drupal core allows SQL Injection.\n\nThis issue affects Drupal core: from 8.9.0 before 10.4.10, from 10.5.0 before 10.5.10, from 10.6.0 before 10.6.9, from 11.0.0 before 11.1.10, from 11.2.0 before 11.2.12, from 11.3.0 before 11.3.10.","created_at":"2026-06-07 21:20:10","updated_at":"2026-06-07 21:20:26","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 21:20:12","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 22:36:41","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1261930993","cve_id":"CVE-2026-4480","name":"CVE-2026-4480","owner":"robinxiang","full_name":"robinxiang/CVE-2026-4480","html_url":"https://github.com/robinxiang/CVE-2026-4480","description":"Exploit CVE-2026-4480","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A flaw was found in the Samba printing subsystem. Samba passes the client-controlled job description string to the command configured with the \"print command\" setting via the \"%J\"\nsubstitution character without escaping shell meta characters. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability by sending a specially crafted print job description that contains unescaped shell characters. This could lead to remote code execution on the affected system.","created_at":"2026-06-07 19:53:18","updated_at":"2026-06-07 19:57:43","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 19:57:40","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 22:36:41","cvss_score":9,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1261642101","cve_id":"CVE-2025-57819","name":"CVE-2025-57819-exploit","owner":"Jeanback1","full_name":"Jeanback1/CVE-2025-57819-exploit","html_url":"https://github.com/Jeanback1/CVE-2025-57819-exploit","description":"FreePBX Pre-Auth SQLi to RCE (CVE-2025-57819) — All-in-One Exploit","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"FreePBX is an open-source web-based graphical user interface. FreePBX 15, 16, and 17 endpoints are vulnerable due to insufficiently sanitized user-supplied data allowing unauthenticated access to FreePBX Administrator leading to arbitrary database manipulation and remote code execution. This issue has been patched in endpoint versions 15.0.66, 16.0.89, and 17.0.3.","created_at":"2026-06-07 09:54:28","updated_at":"2026-06-07 09:58:03","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 09:58:00","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 16:36:40","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1261577847","cve_id":"CVE-2019-5513","name":"CVE-2019-5513-scanner","owner":"sudosu01","full_name":"sudosu01/CVE-2019-5513-scanner","html_url":"https://github.com/sudosu01/CVE-2019-5513-scanner","description":"The VMWare Horizon Connection Server is often used as an internet-facing gateway to an organization’s virtual desktop environment (VDI). Until recently, most of these installations exposed the Connection Server’s internal name, the gateway’s internal IP address, and the Active Directory domain to unauthenticated attackers.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"VMware Horizon Connection Server (7.x before 7.8, 7.5.x before 7.5.2, 6.x before 6.2.8) contains an information disclosure vulnerability. Successful exploitation of this issue may allow disclosure of internal domain names, the Connection Server’s internal name, or the gateway’s internal IP address.","created_at":"2026-06-07 07:01:51","updated_at":"2026-06-07 07:11:04","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 07:11:00","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 10:36:37","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1261529108","cve_id":"CVE-2025-57819","name":"CVE-2025-57819-poc","owner":"b4sh2","full_name":"b4sh2/CVE-2025-57819-poc","html_url":"https://github.com/b4sh2/CVE-2025-57819-poc","description":"CVE-2025-57819 poc","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"FreePBX is an open-source web-based graphical user interface. FreePBX 15, 16, and 17 endpoints are vulnerable due to insufficiently sanitized user-supplied data allowing unauthenticated access to FreePBX Administrator leading to arbitrary database manipulation and remote code execution. This issue has been patched in endpoint versions 15.0.66, 16.0.89, and 17.0.3.","created_at":"2026-06-07 05:13:34","updated_at":"2026-06-07 05:55:53","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 05:55:50","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 10:36:41","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1261472805","cve_id":"CVE-2026-10580","name":"By-Poloss..-..CVE-2026-10580","owner":"O99099O","full_name":"O99099O/By-Poloss..-..CVE-2026-10580","html_url":"https://github.com/O99099O/By-Poloss..-..CVE-2026-10580","description":"Hippoo Mobile App for WooCommerce <= 1.9.4 - Unauthenticated Authentication Bypass to Administrator Account Takeover","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$19","created_at":"2026-06-07 03:25:04","updated_at":"2026-06-07 03:31:43","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 03:31:39","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 04:36:40","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1261434372","cve_id":"CVE-2026-42926","name":"CVE2026-42926","owner":"ikarolaborda","full_name":"ikarolaborda/CVE2026-42926","html_url":"https://github.com/ikarolaborda/CVE2026-42926","description":"Controlled NGINX HTTP/2 frame injection lab for CVE-2026-42926 patch validation and defensive research","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"When NGINX Open Source is configured to proxy HTTP/2 traffic by setting proxy_http_version to 2, and also uses proxy_set_body, an attacker may be able to inject frame headers and payload bytes to the upstream peer.  Note: Software versions which have reached End of Technical Support (EoTS) are not evaluated.","created_at":"2026-06-07 02:19:16","updated_at":"2026-06-07 02:19:29","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 02:19:19","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 04:36:40","cvss_score":5.8,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1261410583","cve_id":"CVE-2023-44487","name":"http2-security-lab","owner":"madhantr0","full_name":"madhantr0/http2-security-lab","html_url":"https://github.com/madhantr0/http2-security-lab","description":"HTTP/2 attack simulation & defense lab - Slowloris, Rapid Reset (CVE-2023-44487), HPACK Bomb attacks with 5 layered defenses. Built in pure Python with raw sockets and h2 library.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The HTTP/2 protocol allows a denial of service (server resource consumption) because request cancellation can reset many streams quickly, as exploited in the wild in August through October 2023.","created_at":"2026-06-07 01:41:14","updated_at":"2026-06-07 02:02:50","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 02:02:46","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 04:36:39","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1261408109","cve_id":"CVE-2024-54887","name":"CVE-2024-54887-PoC","owner":"Gumbraise","full_name":"Gumbraise/CVE-2024-54887-PoC","html_url":"https://github.com/Gumbraise/CVE-2024-54887-PoC","description":"TypeScript PoC for CVE-2024-54887 (TP-Link TL-WR940N authenticated RCE)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"TP-Link TL-WR940N V3 and V4 with firmware 3.16.9 and earlier contain a buffer overflow via the dnsserver1 and dnsserver2 parameters at /userRpm/Wan6to4TunnelCfgRpm.htm. This vulnerability allows an authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the remote device in the context of the root user.","created_at":"2026-06-07 01:37:33","updated_at":"2026-06-07 01:37:41","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 01:37:36","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 04:36:39","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1261390893","cve_id":"CVE-2026-45585","name":"yellowkey-bitlocker-222","owner":"SmashMythAmp","full_name":"SmashMythAmp/yellowkey-bitlocker-222","html_url":"https://github.com/SmashMythAmp/yellowkey-bitlocker-222","description":"yellowkey  bitlocker github vulnerability  bypass  cve-2026-45585 windows 11 security zero day exploit winre recovery mode poc nightmare eclipse chaotic eclipse exploit tool usb attack encryption hack script mitigation guide fstx winpeshl shell unpatched fix tool","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Microsoft is aware of a security feature bypass vulnerability in Windows publicly referred to as &quot;YellowKey&quot;. The proof of concept for this vulnerability has been made public violating coordinated vulnerability best practices.\nWe are issuing this CVE to provide mitigation guidance that can be implemented to protect against this vulnerability until the security update is made available.","created_at":"2026-06-07 01:11:44","updated_at":"2026-06-07 01:12:27","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 01:12:24","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 04:36:40","cvss_score":6.8,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1261374107","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-706","owner":"RoyalViceroyBear","full_name":"RoyalViceroyBear/CVE-2026-41089-706","html_url":"https://github.com/RoyalViceroyBear/CVE-2026-41089-706","description":"CVE-2026-41089 PoC — Netlogon CLDAP stack buffer overflow (CVSS 9.8 CRITICAL)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Stack-based buffer overflow in Windows Netlogon allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-07 00:47:31","updated_at":"2026-06-07 00:48:41","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 00:48:38","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 04:36:40","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1261368744","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-245","owner":"CrimsonKingfisher","full_name":"CrimsonKingfisher/CVE-2026-41089-245","html_url":"https://github.com/CrimsonKingfisher/CVE-2026-41089-245","description":"CVE-2026-41089 PoC — Netlogon CLDAP stack buffer overflow (CVSS 9.8 CRITICAL)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Stack-based buffer overflow in Windows Netlogon allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-07 00:39:39","updated_at":"2026-06-07 00:40:17","pushed_at":"2026-06-07 00:40:14","inserted_at":"2026-06-07 04:36:40","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1261367022","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-397","owner":"Pow