clipse exploit tool usb attack encryption hack script mitigation guide fstx winpeshl shell unpatched fix tool","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Microsoft is aware of a security feature bypass vulnerability in Windows publicly referred to as &quot;YellowKey&quot;. The proof of concept for this vulnerability has been made public violating coordinated vulnerability best practices.\nWe are issuing this CVE to provide mitigation guidance that can be implemented to protect against this vulnerability until the security update is made available.","created_at":"2026-06-06 19:59:15","updated_at":"2026-06-06 19:59:56","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 19:59:54","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 22:36:41","cvss_score":6.8,"severity":"MEDIUM"},{"id":"1261179432","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-274","owner":"Fuchsiafromcurl","full_name":"Fuchsiafromcurl/CVE-2026-41089-274","html_url":"https://github.com/Fuchsiafromcurl/CVE-2026-41089-274","description":"CVE-2026-41089 PoC — Netlogon CLDAP stack buffer overflow (CVSS 9.8 CRITICAL)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Stack-based buffer overflow in Windows Netlogon allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-06 19:46:59","updated_at":"2026-06-06 19:47:00","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 19:47:00","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 22:36:41","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1261020599","cve_id":"CVE-2026-24849","name":"CVE-2026-24849","owner":"doany1","full_name":"doany1/CVE-2026-24849","html_url":"https://github.com/doany1/CVE-2026-24849","description":"Proof-of-concept exploit for CVE-2026-24849, an authenticated path-traversal / arbitrary file read in OpenEMR's Fax/SMS (EtherFax) module. Any authenticated user  regardless of privilege level  can read arbitrary files from the server filesystem as the web-server user (database credentials, patient documents/PHI, /etc/passwd, …","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"OpenEMR is a free and open source electronic health records and medical practice management application. Prior to version 7.0.4, the `disposeDocument()` method in `EtherFaxActions.php` allows authenticated users to read arbitrary files from the server filesystem. Any authenticated user (regardless of privilege level) can exploit this vulnerability to read sensitive files. Version 7.0.4 patches the issue.","created_at":"2026-06-06 15:19:10","updated_at":"2026-06-06 15:22:12","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 15:20:45","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 16:36:40","cvss_score":10,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1261003065","cve_id":"CVE-2026-42588","name":"CVE-2026-42588","owner":"hnytgl","full_name":"hnytgl/CVE-2026-42588","html_url":"https://github.com/hnytgl/CVE-2026-42588","description":"CVE-2026-42588 - Apache ActiveMQ Jolokia 远程代码执行漏洞利用 (RCE Exploit)","stargazers_count":"1","vuln_description":"$1b","created_at":"2026-06-06 14:47:28","updated_at":"2026-06-06 15:20:04","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 15:20:00","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 16:36:40","cvss_score":8.1,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1260986879","cve_id":"CVE-2023-46604","name":"CVE-2023-46604-RCE","owner":"REGGYRAIDER","full_name":"REGGYRAIDER/CVE-2023-46604-RCE","html_url":"https://github.com/REGGYRAIDER/CVE-2023-46604-RCE","description":"CVE-2023-46604-RCE exploit with Linux reverse shell payload","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Apache ActiveMQ is vulnerable to Remote Code Execution.The vulnerability may allow a remote attacker with network access to a broker to run arbitrary shell commands by manipulating serialized class types in the OpenWire protocol to cause the broker to instantiate any class on the classpath. \n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 5.15.16, 5.16.7, 5.17.6, or 5.18.3, which fixes this issue.","created_at":"2026-06-06 14:17:40","updated_at":"2026-06-06 14:18:26","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 14:18:22","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 16:36:39","cvss_score":10,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260976509","cve_id":"CVE-2026-23744","name":"CVE-2026-23744","owner":"oryk0","full_name":"oryk0/CVE-2026-23744","html_url":"https://github.com/oryk0/CVE-2026-23744","description":"CVE-2026-23744 Reverse shell","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"MCPJam inspector is the local-first development platform for MCP servers. Versions 1.4.2 and earlier are vulnerable to remote code execution (RCE) vulnerability, which allows an attacker to send a crafted HTTP request that triggers the installation of an MCP server, leading to RCE. Since MCPJam inspector by default listens on 0.0.0.0 instead of 127.0.0.1, an attacker can trigger the RCE remotely via a simple HTTP request. Version 1.4.3 contains a patch.","created_at":"2026-06-06 13:57:39","updated_at":"2026-06-06 14:01:55","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 14:01:52","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 16:36:40","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260960901","cve_id":"CVE-2026-20245","name":"CVE-2026-20245","owner":"HORKimhab","full_name":"HORKimhab/CVE-2026-20245","html_url":"https://github.com/HORKimhab/CVE-2026-20245","description":"CVE-2026-20245 - Cisco SD-WAN - Draft","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$1c","created_at":"2026-06-06 13:26:16","updated_at":"2026-06-06 13:26:22","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 13:26:19","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 16:36:40","cvss_score":7.8,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1260824054","cve_id":"CVE-2025-55182","name":"react2shell","owner":"rvzsec","full_name":"rvzsec/react2shell","html_url":"https://github.com/rvzsec/react2shell","description":"react2shell - CVE-2025-55182 (Next.js: CVE-2025-66478) - Unauthenticated RCE in React Server Components (Flight Protocol) - PoC Exploit","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A pre-authentication remote code execution vulnerability exists in React Server Components versions 19.0.0, 19.1.0, 19.1.1, and 19.2.0 including the following packages: react-server-dom-parcel, react-server-dom-turbopack, and react-server-dom-webpack. The vulnerable code unsafely deserializes payloads from HTTP requests to Server Function endpoints.","created_at":"2026-06-06 08:09:56","updated_at":"2026-06-06 08:15:25","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 08:15:21","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 10:36:41","cvss_score":10,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260742161","cve_id":"CVE-2026-34908","name":"CVE-2026-34908-check","owner":"BishopFox","full_name":"BishopFox/CVE-2026-34908-check","html_url":"https://github.com/BishopFox/CVE-2026-34908-check","description":"Safely detect whether a UniFi OS Server is vulnerable to CVE-2026-34908","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"A malicious actor with access to the network could exploit an Improper Access Control vulnerability found in UniFi OS devices to make unauthorized changes to the system.","created_at":"2026-06-06 05:28:38","updated_at":"2026-06-06 05:28:59","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 05:28:52","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 10:36:41","cvss_score":10,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260590626","cve_id":"CVE-2026-25860","name":"CVE-2026-25860","owner":"partywavesec","full_name":"partywavesec/CVE-2026-25860","html_url":"https://github.com/partywavesec/CVE-2026-25860","description":"CVE-2026-25860 POC git","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-06-06 01:52:51","updated_at":"2026-06-06 02:09:15","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 02:09:10","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 04:36:40","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1260519283","cve_id":"CVE-2026-9256","name":"Nginx-chain-Rift-Poolslip","owner":"y198nt","full_name":"y198nt/Nginx-chain-Rift-Poolslip","html_url":"https://github.com/y198nt/Nginx-chain-Rift-Poolslip","description":"Nginx RCE chain PoC with CVE-2026-9256 and CVE-2026-42945","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"NGINX Plus and NGINX Open Source have a vulnerability in the ngx_http_rewrite_module module. This vulnerability exists when a rewrite directive uses a regex pattern with distinct, overlapping Perl-Compatible Regular Expression (PCRE) captures (for example, ^/((.*))$) and a replacement string that references multiple such captures (for example, $1$2) in a redirect or arguments context. An unauthenticated attacker along with conditions beyond their control can exploit this vulnerability by sending crafted HTTP requests. This may cause a heap buffer overflow in the NGINX worker process leading to a restart. Additionally, attackers can execute code on systems with Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR) disabled or when the attacker can bypass ASLR. \n\n\nNote: Software versions which have reached End of Technical Support (EoTS) are not evaluated.","created_at":"2026-06-06 00:21:38","updated_at":"2026-06-06 01:03:31","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 01:03:27","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 04:36:40","cvss_score":8.1,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1260454962","cve_id":"CVE-2026-1238","name":"Breaking-AWS-IAM-Privilege-Escalation-via-Mis-Evaluated-Policy-Conditions-CVE-2026-1238-","owner":"mrk336","full_name":"mrk336/Breaking-AWS-IAM-Privilege-Escalation-via-Mis-Evaluated-Policy-Conditions-CVE-2026-1238-","html_url":"https://github.com/mrk336/Breaking-AWS-IAM-Privilege-Escalation-via-Mis-Evaluated-Policy-Conditions-CVE-2026-1238-","description":"This research analyzes CVE‑2026‑1238, a flaw in AWS IAM where policy conditions are mis‑evaluated, enabling stealthy privilege escalation. It breaks down the root cause, real‑world impact, and practical mitigation steps to help teams secure their cloud environments.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The SlimStat Analytics plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to Stored Cross-Site Scripting via the 'fh' (fingerprint) parameter in all versions up to, and including, 5.3.5 due to insufficient input sanitization and output escaping. This makes it possible for unauthenticated attackers to inject arbitrary web scripts in pages that will execute whenever a user accesses an injected page.","created_at":"2026-06-05 23:07:23","updated_at":"2026-06-06 03:21:19","pushed_at":"2026-06-06 03:21:15","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 04:36:40","cvss_score":7.2,"severity":"HIGH"},{"id":"1260429884","cve_id":"CVE-2026-48866","name":"CVE-2026-48866","owner":"0xABCD01","full_name":"0xABCD01/CVE-2026-48866","html_url":"https://github.com/0xABCD01/CVE-2026-48866","description":"CVE-2026-48866 — Gravity Forms <= 2.10.0.1 Arbitrary File Deletion via Path Traversal (CVSS 9.6)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal') vulnerability in Rocketgenius Inc. Gravity Forms allows Path Traversal.\n\nThis issue affects Gravity Forms: from n/a through 2.10.0.1.","created_at":"2026-06-05 22:38:07","updated_at":"2026-06-05 22:42:27","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 22:38:27","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 04:36:40","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1260390892","cve_id":"CVE-2010-2075","name":"cve-2010-2075-analysis","owner":"mishaqdev","full_name":"mishaqdev/cve-2010-2075-analysis","html_url":"https://github.com/mishaqdev/cve-2010-2075-analysis","description":"Technical writeup and penetration testing report for CVE-2010-2075, demonstrating UnrealIRCd backdoor exploitation and remediation.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"UnrealIRCd 3.2.8.1, as distributed on certain mirror sites from November 2009 through June 2010, contains an externally introduced modification (Trojan Horse) in the DEBUG3_DOLOG_SYSTEM macro, which allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands.","created_at":"2026-06-05 21:51:41","updated_at":"2026-06-05 23:27:01","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 23:26:56","inserted_at":"2026-06-06 04:36:36","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1260309683","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-686","owner":"GalleryJoiner","full_name":"GalleryJoiner/CVE-2026-41089-686","html_url":"https://github.com/GalleryJoiner/CVE-2026-41089-686","description":"CVE-2026-41089 PoC — Netlogon CLDAP stack buffer overflow (CVSS 9.8 CRITICAL)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Stack-based buffer overflow in Windows Netlogon allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-05 20:05:43","updated_at":"2026-06-05 20:06:20","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 20:06:18","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:41","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260306987","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-277","owner":"Planetpliexpose","full_name":"Planetpliexpose/CVE-2026-41089-277","html_url":"https://github.com/Planetpliexpose/CVE-2026-41089-277","description":"CVE-2026-41089 PoC — Netlogon CLDAP stack buffer overflow (CVSS 9.8 CRITICAL)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Stack-based buffer overflow in Windows Netlogon allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-05 20:02:12","updated_at":"2026-06-05 20:02:59","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 20:02:55","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:41","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260280302","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-552","owner":"SkySmokeMoat","full_name":"SkySmokeMoat/CVE-2026-41089-552","html_url":"https://github.com/SkySmokeMoat/CVE-2026-41089-552","description":"CVE-2026-41089 PoC — Netlogon CLDAP stack buffer overflow (CVSS 9.8 CRITICAL)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Stack-based buffer overflow in Windows Netlogon allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-05 19:26:59","updated_at":"2026-06-05 19:27:45","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 19:27:43","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:41","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260262202","cve_id":"CVE-2010-0832","name":"Popcorn-TJNULL-OSCP-","owner":"R3fr4kt","full_name":"R3fr4kt/Popcorn-TJNULL-OSCP-","html_url":"https://github.com/R3fr4kt/Popcorn-TJNULL-OSCP-","description":"Popcorn HTB write-up covering advanced directory fuzzing, file upload bypass via magic numbers/extension spoofing using Burp Suite, and privilege escalation via CVE-2010-0832 (PAM MOTD File Tampering).","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":null,"created_at":"2026-06-05 19:04:08","updated_at":"2026-06-05 19:06:16","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 19:05:13","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:36","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1260224280","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-663","owner":"senseibreathhovel","full_name":"senseibreathhovel/CVE-2026-41089-663","html_url":"https://github.com/senseibreathhovel/CVE-2026-41089-663","description":"CVE-2026-41089 PoC — Netlogon CLDAP stack buffer overflow (CVSS 9.8 CRITICAL)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Stack-based buffer overflow in Windows Netlogon allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-05 18:17:24","updated_at":"2026-06-05 18:18:01","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 18:17:59","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:41","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260214355","cve_id":"CVE-2026-40072","name":"cve-2026-40072-ssrf-lab","owner":"u1tr0nex","full_name":"u1tr0nex/cve-2026-40072-ssrf-lab","html_url":"https://github.com/u1tr0nex/cve-2026-40072-ssrf-lab","description":"Hands-on lab for CVE-2026-40072 — SSRF vulnerability in web3.py via CCIP Read (EIP-3668)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"$1d","created_at":"2026-06-05 18:05:30","updated_at":"2026-06-05 18:13:51","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 18:13:10","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:41","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1260193826","cve_id":"CVE-2026-3300","name":"CVE-2026-3300","owner":"HORKimhab","full_name":"HORKimhab/CVE-2026-3300","html_url":"https://github.com/HORKimhab/CVE-2026-3300","description":"CVE-2026-3300","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"The Everest Forms Pro plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to Remote Code Execution via PHP Code Injection in all versions up to, and including, 1.9.12. This is due to the Calculation Addon's process_filter() function concatenating user-submitted form field values into a PHP code string without proper escaping before passing it to eval(). The sanitize_text_field() function applied to input does not escape single quotes or other PHP code context characters. This makes it possible for unauthenticated attackers to inject and execute arbitrary PHP code on the server by submitting a crafted value in any string-type form field (text, email, URL, select, radio) when a form uses the \"Complex Calculation\" feature.","created_at":"2026-06-05 17:40:33","updated_at":"2026-06-05 18:02:28","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 18:01:51","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:41","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1260193269","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-984","owner":"sidechairmanblast","full_name":"sidechairmanblast/CVE-2026-41089-984","html_url":"https://github.com/sidechairmanblast/CVE-2026-41089-984","description":"CVE-2026-41089 PoC — Netlogon CLDAP stack buffer overflow (CVSS 9.8 CRITICAL)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Stack-based buffer overflow in Windows Netlogon allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-05 17:39:56","updated_at":"2026-06-05 17:39:56","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 17:39:56","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:41","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260179301","cve_id":"CVE-2026-41089","name":"CVE-2026-41089-699","owner":"System32manager","full_name":"System32manager/CVE-2026-41089-699","html_url":"https://github.com/System32manager/CVE-2026-41089-699","description":"CVE-2026-41089 PoC — Netlogon CLDAP stack buffer overflow (CVSS 9.8 CRITICAL)","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Stack-based buffer overflow in Windows Netlogon allows an unauthorized attacker to execute code over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-05 17:23:12","updated_at":"2026-06-05 17:23:36","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 17:23:32","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:41","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260132319","cve_id":"CVE-2026-23744","name":"CVE-2026-23744-poc","owner":"keeieb79","full_name":"keeieb79/CVE-2026-23744-poc","html_url":"https://github.com/keeieb79/CVE-2026-23744-poc","description":"cve-2026-23744 python exploit","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"MCPJam inspector is the local-first development platform for MCP servers. Versions 1.4.2 and earlier are vulnerable to remote code execution (RCE) vulnerability, which allows an attacker to send a crafted HTTP request that triggers the installation of an MCP server, leading to RCE. Since MCPJam inspector by default listens on 0.0.0.0 instead of 127.0.0.1, an attacker can trigger the RCE remotely via a simple HTTP request. Version 1.4.3 contains a patch.","created_at":"2026-06-05 16:27:43","updated_at":"2026-06-05 16:38:39","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 16:38:07","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 22:36:41","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260061257","cve_id":"CVE-2026-26179","name":"CVE-2026-26179","owner":"nikosecurity","full_name":"nikosecurity/CVE-2026-26179","html_url":"https://github.com/nikosecurity/CVE-2026-26179","description":"PoC for CVE-2026-26179 / ZDI-26-276, my very own Secure Kernel bug","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Double free in Windows Kernel allows an authorized attacker to elevate privileges locally.","created_at":"2026-06-05 14:53:01","updated_at":"2026-06-05 15:08:59","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 14:57:48","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 16:36:39","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1260046729","cve_id":"CVE-2025-53779","name":"Active-Directory-BadSuccessor","owner":"Musa-xvi","full_name":"Musa-xvi/Active-Directory-BadSuccessor","html_url":"https://github.com/Musa-xvi/Active-Directory-BadSuccessor","description":"A TryHackme room covering the CVE-2025-53779 exploitation using windows","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"Relative path traversal in Windows Kerberos allows an authorized attacker to elevate privileges over a network.","created_at":"2026-06-05 14:30:47","updated_at":"2026-06-05 14:30:52","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 14:30:48","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 16:36:39","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"},{"id":"1260039943","cve_id":"CVE-2026-23744","name":"CVE-2026-23744-MCPJAM-RCE-exploit","owner":"Dahalsamir","full_name":"Dahalsamir/CVE-2026-23744-MCPJAM-RCE-exploit","html_url":"https://github.com/Dahalsamir/CVE-2026-23744-MCPJAM-RCE-exploit","description":"This Python proof-of-concept targets a vulnerable MCP (Model Context Protocol) service exposed by the target application. The vulnerability allows an attacker to supply arbitrary server configuration parameters through the /api/mcp/connect endpoint.","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"MCPJam inspector is the local-first development platform for MCP servers. Versions 1.4.2 and earlier are vulnerable to remote code execution (RCE) vulnerability, which allows an attacker to send a crafted HTTP request that triggers the installation of an MCP server, leading to RCE. Since MCPJam inspector by default listens on 0.0.0.0 instead of 127.0.0.1, an attacker can trigger the RCE remotely via a simple HTTP request. Version 1.4.3 contains a patch.","created_at":"2026-06-05 14:19:26","updated_at":"2026-06-05 14:22:33","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 14:22:29","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 16:36:39","cvss_score":9.8,"severity":"CRITICAL"},{"id":"1260035130","cve_id":"CVE-2011-2523","name":"vsftpd-234-backdoor","owner":"H4R335HR","full_name":"H4R335HR/vsftpd-234-backdoor","html_url":"https://github.com/H4R335HR/vsftpd-234-backdoor","description":"Dependency-free interactive Python exploit for the vsftpd 2.3.4 backdoor (CVE-2011-2523).","stargazers_count":"0","vuln_description":"vsftpd 2.3.4 downloaded between 20110630 and 20110703 contains a backdoor which opens a shell on port 6200/tcp.","created_at":"2026-06-05 14:10:41","updated_at":"2026-06-05 14:17:56","pushed_at":"2026-06-05 14:17:52","inserted_at":"2026-06-05 16:36:36","cvss_score":null,"severity":"UNKNOWN"}]}]}]
